Anonymous Sun 18 Feb 2024 11:31:17 No.63391987 Report
Quoted By:
>>63391541
I started with Enemy Within. I picked up the "commander edition" (the advantage of playing games years later is that you get the whole game at once at a lower price).
This expansion adds improvements that fix the pace of the game quite well while adding nice extras to the lore.
It's also just the best of the Firaxis games.

Just be prepared for the game to glitch and crash in the late game. Try not to save scum (you should run at least one failing playthrough all the way to the end just to see the canon fail state), but even I wouldn't use the game's Ironman function for a single save file, just because of now often the game can just break.

Oh and if you get to the sequel and want to do the same thing by activating all the content at once in XCOM 2, don't. The DLC isn't built to be active together (specifically War of the Chosen and Alien Hunters. You can activate all the equipment and cosmetics DLCs you want), and the in game option to integrate them together does so by taking out some introductory content.
